HEADWORD: gridiron-tailed lizard
<hw>gridiron-tailed lizard</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a lizard having a
long tail with black bands (<spn>Callisaurus draconoides</spn>), which
lives in the deserts of the southwestern U. S. and Mexico; called also
<altname>zebra-tailed lizard</altname>.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
